Class LPReader

java.lang.Object
  LPReader

public class LPReader
extends java.lang.Object

A class to read linear programs from .lp files. Initialise with the file name and invoke the method readLP() to parse an lp from an .lp file. After successful reading all data is held in various arrays which can be accessed via class methods. Debug output can be switched on by an additional parameter to the constructor.
Note that the parser cannot yet handle integer and binary variables!
